sh literature. Spenser, Donne, Marvell, Defoe, Swift, Fanny Burney, Austen, Byron, Thackeray, Lewis Carroll, Tennyson, George Eliot, Sylvia Plath, and Doris Lessing--all hid their names. With great lucidity and wit, Anonymity tells the stories of these and many other writers, providing a fast-paced, entertaining, and informative tour through the history of English literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aAbbott, Chief Justice.  aAdelphi.  aAinsworth, Harrison.  aAll the Year Round.  aAnti-Corn Law Circular.  aAytoun, William.  aBallantyne, James.  aBarber, John.  aBerkeley, Grantley.  aBrussels.  aBurnet, Gilbert.  aCadell, Thomas.  aCambridge University.  aCaroline, Queen.  aChapman, John.  aChristian Remembrancer.  aCommonwealth.  aCritical Review.  aDaily Chronicle.  aDonne, John.  aDryden, John.  aDusautoy family.  aEast India Company.  aEdinburgh Review.  aEdinburgh.  aFaber and Faber.  aFerguson, John.  aFielding, Sarah.  aFortnightly.  aFrench Revolution.  aGarrick Club, London.  aGentleman's Magazine.  aGlasgow Sentinel.  aGunpowder Plot.  aHallam, Arthur Henry.  aHardy, Thomas.  aHazlitt, Sarah.  aHigginson, Henry.  aJacobite Rebellion (1745).  aJohn Bull Magazine.  aKing, Larry.  aKnight, Fanny.  aLeighton, Alexander.  aLewes, Agnes.  aLiddell, Alice.  aLiterary Journal.  aLondon Chronicle.  aLondon Review of Books.  aMartineau, Lucy.  aMary, Queen.  aNew Monthly Magazine.  aOld Testament.  aOldham, John.  acirculating libraries.  adedications.  amock books.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691230924zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691230924423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.c